</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6AFFE6FE8172D7DDB6FDEE" box="[382,680,509,533]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthioides">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FE8172D7DDB6FDEE" box="[382,680,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Pardaleodes xanthioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="F330D8A47E6AFFE6FD5072D4DC0AFDED" box="[687,788,510,534]" name="Netherlands" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Holland</collectingCountry>
, 1892.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6AFFE6FF3F7104DABEFCD2" blockId="24.[192,1441,558,809]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FF3F7104DE51FDBD" bold="true" box="[192,335,558,582]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus to 
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FDE27104DD85FDBD" box="[541,667,558,582]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Hollandus</emphasis>
Larsen and Collins, 2015 (
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6AFFE6FC2A7104DB17FDBD" box="[981,1033,558,582]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6AFFE6FB977104DA81FDBD" authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1892" box="[1128,1439,558,582]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pardaleodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthopeplus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FB977104DA81FDBD" box="[1128,1439,558,582]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Pardaleodes xanthopeplus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingCountry id="F330D8A47E6AFFE6FF3F7165DE3BFD9C" box="[192,293,591,615]" name="Netherlands" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Holland</collectingCountry>
, 1892), formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6AFFE6FD9D7165DCA0FD9C" authority="Aurivillius, 1925" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1925" box="[610,958,591,615]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Paronymus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FD9D7165DDF3FD9D" box="[610,749,591,614]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Paronymus</emphasis>
Aurivillius, 1925
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6AFFE6FC337165DB1CFD9C" box="[972,1026,591,615]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6AFFE6FB9B7165DFE0FD7C" authority="Hewitson, 1876" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligora">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FB9B7165DA00FD9D" box="[1124,1310,590,614]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Hesperia ligora</emphasis>
Hewitson, 1876
</taxonomicName>
), but is not monophyletic with it (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E6AFFE6FD557145DDEAFD7C" box="[682,756,623,647]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="22.[192,275,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,215,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,213,1385]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 9. Genomic trees of Astictopterini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677253/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Keys to VII. 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E6AFFE6FC5F7145DCE7FD7C" box="[928,1017,623,647]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15316" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" unit="in" value="45.4">45.4 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E6AFFE6FBFD715ADBBAFD7C" author="Evans" box="[1026,1188,623,647]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans (1937)</bibRefCitation>
and differs from its relatives by narrow, beak-like uncus; tegumen narrowing into uncus gradually, their junctions slightly concave in ventral view; lack of gnathos; harpe gradually upturned, finely serrated at its short but nearly dorsal margin, with a tooth directed dorsad near its base; hindwing outer margin and tornus brown below. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly822.30.12:C365T, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E6AFFE6FB1B71DBDA4EFCF2" box="[1252,1360,753,777]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" value="1089-08-04">1089.8.4</date>
:G53A, aly164.3.1:A811G, aly5294.20.2:A547A (not T), aly5294.20.2:A548A (not C), aly838.12.1: 
<specimenCode id="DB81304F7E6AFFE6FB11703BDA33FCD2" box="[1262,1325,785,809]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">T458</specimenCode>
T (not A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E6AFFE6FF3F7068DC28FC20" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6AFFE6FF3F7068DBCDFC81" blockId="24.[192,1440,834,891]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FF3F7068DE45FCA1" bold="true" box="[192,347,834,858]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, fusion of the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6AFFE6FB3B7068DBE7FCA1" box="[1220,1273,834,858]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
species name with the genus name where it was placed previously: 
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FCAF7048DC82FC81" box="[848,924,866,890]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Xanth</emphasis>
[ioides] and [Par] 
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FB917049DBD2FC81" box="[1134,1228,867,890]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">onymus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6AFFE6FF3F70B8DCA0FC51" blockId="24.[192,958,914,939]" box="[192,958,914,939]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FF3F70B8DEAEFC51" bold="true" box="[192,432,914,938]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6AFFE6FE1270B9DD3CFC50" box="[493,546,915,939]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6AFFE6FD4270B8DCA9FC51" authorityName="Holland" authorityYear="1892" box="[701,951,914,938]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Xanthodisca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="astrape">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FD4270B8DCA9FC51" box="[701,951,914,938]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Xanthodisca astrape</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6AFFE6FF3F70E9DC28FC20" blockId="24.[192,822,963,987]" box="[192,822,963,987]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6AFFE6FF3F70E9DE62FC20" bold="true" box="[192,380,963,987]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Tribe Astictopterini Swinhoe, 1912.
</paragraph>
